<subSubSection id="EBF5653D9E49FF81FD697753FB3A102D" pageId="77" pageNumber="77" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="A35036B69E49FF81FD697753FB9513A4" blockId="77.[701,1228,723,1632]" pageId="77" pageNumber="77">
COMMENTS: In the original description, Brehm said that of 
<specimenCount id="B5E9FD3F9E49FF81FC1C7772FBAF1532" box="[943,1113,872,895]" pageId="77" pageNumber="77" type="generic">175 specimens</specimenCount>
of crossbills in his collection, he had two specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="64EF4D359E49FF81FD5177B9FC3D15F7" box="[738,971,931,954]" class="Aves" family="Aves (awaiting allocation)" genus="Crucirostra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Aves (awaiting allocation)" pageId="77" pageNumber="77" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pseudopityopsittacus">
<emphasis id="919BEAA49E49FF81FD5177B9FC3D15F7" box="[738,971,931,954]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="77">pseudopityopsittacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a male collected on ‘‘ 
<date id="D75110769E49FF81FD7A77DBFC6A159B" box="[713,924,961,983]" pageId="77" pageNumber="77" value="1817-02-17">17 February 1817</date>
’’ in the Roda Valley and a female collected on 
<date id="D75110769E49FF81FC0277C5FB8F15B9" box="[945,1145,990,1012]" pageId="77" pageNumber="77" value="1834-10-20">
20 October 
<quantity id="64179B539E49FF81FBF177C5FB8F15B9" box="[1090,1145,991,1012]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.65836" pageId="77" pageNumber="77" unit="in" value="1834.0">1834</quantity>
</date>
in the neighborhood of Greiz. The date ‘‘1817’’ is apparently a slip of the pen, as the original Brehm label gives the date as 
<date id="D75110769E49FF81FB84702DFD011224" pageId="77" pageNumber="77" value="1834-02-17">17 February 1834</date>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="C77E4B479E49FF81FCB1704FFC271227" author="Hartert, E." box="[770,977,1108,1130]" pageId="77" pageNumber="77" pagination="4 - 63" refId="ref118974" refString="Hartert, E. 1918. Types of birds in the Tring Museum. A. Types in the Brehm Collection. Novitates Zoologicae 25: 4 - 63." type="journal article" year="1918">Hartert (1918: 12)</bibRefCitation>
listed this male as the type, thereby designating it the 
<typeStatus id="7C5488149E49FF81FB8C7068FB5E12C5" box="[1087,1192,1138,1160]" pageId="77" pageNumber="77">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="64EF4D359E49FF81FD0E7094FC5012E8" box="[701,934,1166,1189]" class="Aves" family="Aves (awaiting allocation)" genus="Crucirostra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Aves (awaiting allocation)" pageId="77" pageNumber="77" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pseudopityopsittacus">
<emphasis id="919BEAA49E49FF81FD0E7094FC5012E8" box="[701,934,1166,1189]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="77">pseudopityopsittacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. He further commented: ‘‘The name 
<emphasis id="919BEAA49E49FF81FCE070B6FBCA128E" box="[851,1084,1196,1219]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="77">pseudopytiopsittacus</emphasis>
is very descriptive, as it is a real giant of 
<emphasis id="919BEAA49E49FF81FB8670D1FCCE12B0" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="77">
<taxonomicName id="64EF4D359E49FF81FB8670D1FB3E12AD" box="[1077,1224,1227,1248]" class="Aves" family="Fringillidae" genus="Loxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="77" pageNumber="77" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="curvir">Loxia curvir</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="64EF4D359E49FF81FD0E70F2FCCE12B0" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[701,824,1256,1277]" class="Aves" family="Fringillidae" genus="Loxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="77" pageNumber="77" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="curvirostra">curvirostra</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, though it does not come up to 
<taxonomicName id="64EF4D359E49FF81FB0170F2FC961356" authorityName="Borkhausen" authorityYear="1793" class="Aves" family="Fringillidae" genus="Loxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="77" pageNumber="77" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pytyopsittacus">
<emphasis id="919BEAA49E49FF81FB0170F2FC961356" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="77">L. pytyopsittacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the bill is not so wide, more elongated, especially the under mandible is less broad; the wing measures 
<quantity id="64179B539E49FF81FB9F715AFB5E1318" box="[1068,1192,1344,1365]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.007" pageId="77" pageNumber="77" unit="mm" value="100.7">100.7 mm</quantity>
.’’ I did not find cataloged at AMNH a female collected on 
<date id="D75110769E49FF81FCE97161FBD213DD" box="[858,1060,1403,1425]" pageId="77" pageNumber="77" value="1834-10-20">
20 October 
<quantity id="64179B539E49FF81FC5E7161FBD213DD" box="[1005,1060,1403,1424]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.65836" pageId="77" pageNumber="77" unit="in" value="1834.0">1834</quantity>
</date>
in Greiz and labeled 
<taxonomicName id="64EF4D359E49FF81FCAF7182FBF313E2" box="[796,1029,1432,1455]" class="Aves" family="Aves (awaiting allocation)" genus="Crucirostra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Aves (awaiting allocation)" pageId="77" pageNumber="77" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pseudopityopsittacus">
<emphasis id="919BEAA49E49FF81FCAF7182FBF313E2" box="[796,1029,1432,1455]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="77">pseudopityopsittacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; thus, no specimens cataloged as this form and exchanged to ZFMK would be 
<typeStatus id="7C5488149E49FF81FC0071C9FBA913A4" box="[947,1119,1491,1513]" pageId="77" pageNumber="77">paralectotypes</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A35036B69E49FF81FD6871EBFB3A102D" blockId="77.[701,1228,723,1632]" pageId="77" pageNumber="77">
This form is referred to ‘‘Abbild. Nr. 5’’; the reverse of Brehm’s label of the 
<typeStatus id="7C5488149E49FF81FBD57215FB3A1068" box="[1126,1228,1551,1573]" pageId="77" pageNumber="77">lectotype</typeStatus>
bears ‘‘Nr. 5,’’ corresponding to figure 
<quantity id="64179B539E49FF81FBC57236FB57100F" box="[1142,1185,1580,1602]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.27" pageId="77" pageNumber="77" unit="in" value="5.0">5 in</quantity>
the unnumbered plate in Brehm (1953: opp. p. 182).
</paragraph>
